## Full contents: `org-api-access-token.server.ts`

```1:17:/Users/duhl/git/ui/apps/org-next/src/server/org-api-access-token.server.ts
import { createServerOnlyFn } from "@tanstack/react-start";
import { readAuthenticatedAccessToken } from "./auth-session";

/**
 * Session token when logged in; otherwise a dev-only token when
 * `VITE_ORG_NEXT_BYPASS_AUTH=true` (local backend may ignore auth).
 */
export const resolveOrgApiAccessToken = createServerOnlyFn(
  async (): Promise<string | null> => {
    const devAccessToken = process.env.ORG_NEXT_DEV_ACCESS_TOKEN;
    if (devAccessToken) {
      return devAccessToken;
    }

    return await readAuthenticatedAccessToken();
  },
);
```

**Note:** The JSDoc mentions `VITE_ORG_NEXT_BYPASS_AUTH`; the implemented override is **`ORG_NEXT_DEV_ACCESS_TOKEN`**, not that Vite flag inside this file. Any interaction with bypass auth would be in `readAuthenticatedAccessToken` / session code, not in this small resolver.

